\pard\sl276\slmult1\b Changed:\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sl276\slmult1\b0 Updates the CLI version to 0.12.0.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}From now on, new tabs always open after the last tab. Previously, new tabs were opened after the current tab.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Reimplemented missing LoadSketch in TypeScript.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Adjusts the Output styles to the Java IDE.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Fixed copy for Forum/GitHub. In case of no or empty selection, the entire editor content is copied. Otherwise, the selected text.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}From now on, toggling the serial monitor will dispose the serial monitor view instead of toggling the bottom panel.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Removes the keybinding for indent/outdent lines menu items. The functionality remains the same.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Refined and generalized which tabs are closable and which not. All files that belong to a sketch (SketchLoad) must be non-closeable in normal mode.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Refined new file and rename file. Adjusted the input dialog behavior to the Java IDE.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Made the Daemon output channel more relaxed. It should never activate on Daemon input.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}The board search is fuzzy now.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}We clear the upload/compile consoles before running upload/compile.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Aligned the New and Save As... with the Java IDE.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Rework the menu organization\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}The copy of Arduino CLI embedded in the Arduino Pro IDE installation is always used, rather than picking up an external Arduino CLI installation if it is in PATH.\par

\pard\sl276\slmult1\b Fixed:\b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sl276\slmult1 Makes sure the main sketch file has the focus at app startup without focusing on other editors.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Fixed save as.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Upload using a programmer does not require a serial port.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Fixed serial monitor issue. Previously, the board had to be manually re-selected after an upload.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Fixed deletion. When deleting the main sketch file, the window closes.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Fixed issue when Output grabbed the focus when the user was searching for a board with the board config dialog.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}The Output automatically expands on upload/compile and on errors.\par
{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}Added a workaround for path too long on Windows by removing the YAML VS Code extension from the final app.\par

